

     
       Who needs a dream?  Who needs ambition?  Who'd be the fool  In my position?  Once I had dreams  Now they're obsessions  Hopes became needs  Lovers possessions.  Then they move in  Oh so discreetly  Slowly at first  Smiling too sweetly  I opened doors  They walked right through them  Called me their friend  I hardly knew them.  
     
    
